cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the storage and analysis of large datasets, specifically using graph structures and analysis techniques. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.SI (social and information networks), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.CY (computers and society). However, given the focus on graph databases and analysis, cs.DB and cs.SI are the most likely categories.
